Package com.intellij.util.keyFMap

Interface KeyFMap

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayBackedFMap

    public interface KeyFMap
    An immutable map optimized for storing few Key entries with relatively rare updates. To construct a map, start with EMPTY_MAP and call plus(com.intellij.openapi.util.Key<V>, V) and minus(com.intellij.openapi.util.Key<?>).

    The hashCode() contract conforms to the hashCode() contract of the Map interface: it's the sum of hash codes of its entries, which in turn is calculated as key.hashCode() ^ value.hashCode()

        Returns a KeyFMap which consists of the same elements as this KeyFMap, except the supplied key which is removed. May return itself if the supplied key is absent in this map.

        Returns:

      • get

        <V> V get(Key<V> key)
        Returns a value associated with given key in this KeyFMap, or null if no value is associated. Note that unlike HashMap KeyFMap cannot hold null values.

        Parameters:
        key - a key to get the value associated with
        Returns:
